credit.credit-words: In vain Thou strugglest to get free, I never will unloose my hold! Art Thou the Man that died for me? The secret of Thy love unfold; Wrestling, I will not let Thee go, Till I Thy name, Thy nature know.

direction-type.words: And I am left alone with
Yield to me now, for I am weak,
Speak to my heart, in blessings
And tell me if Thy Name is Love.
